    <a title="Lee" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/626750-lee"><img alt="Lee" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1635863376p2/626750.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/22248641?book_show_action=true">May 14, 2008</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Lee" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Lee" href="/user/show/626750-lee">Lee</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>


          <div><span class="uitext greyText">Recommends it for: </span>
           <span class="uitext reviewText">ryan</span></div>

        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/626750-lee?shelf=own">own</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer22248641" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer3662979926955538074">Amazing book on revelation. I always looked at revelation as more of an isolated concept. This book helped me understand the vital importance of receiving revelation is and how to best prepare to receive it and understand it when it comes, how much it should tie into every aspect of our lives, yet how we should also be spiritually self-sufficient at times. I will definitely be referencing and rereading this book through the future.</span>

          </span>
        </div>


