<span id="freeTextContainer3576791085413090083">This book has some good stories and examples of revelation being received. I think Bro Lund has really tried to explain it so that people would be encouraged to recognize and act on the promptings they receive. However I want quite halfway through when I decided to quit reading. Some of the examples he used I felt brought up doubts that didn’t need to be brought up. Maybe some people have wondered why the Angel Moroni appeared to Mary Whitmer instead of Emma Smith, but that never occurred to me </span>
  <span id="freeText3576791085413090083" style="display:none">This book has some good stories and examples of revelation being received. I think Bro Lund has really tried to explain it so that people would be encouraged to recognize and act on the promptings they receive. However I want quite halfway through when I decided to quit reading. Some of the examples he used I felt brought up doubts that didn’t need to be brought up. Maybe some people have wondered why the Angel Moroni appeared to Mary Whitmer instead of Emma Smith, but that never occurred to me to question. I understand that he would use examples like that to illustrate his point, but I didn’t feel that it was helpful. Anyway, I think overall it was a good book, but I also think the same principles could be learned more succinctly from reading conference talks and the scriptures. </span>
